# Terminology

- The full glossary is normative and must be applied in full:
  - `.cursor/rules/docs/refs-glossary-full.mdc`
- Apply glossary constraints directly:
  - `K8s` with uppercase `K`;
  - `cloud provider` -> "–Њ–±–ї–∞—З–љ—Л–є –њ—А–Њ–≤–∞–є–і–µ—А";
  - `module parameter` -> "–њ–∞—А–∞–Љ–µ—В—А –Љ–Њ–і—Г–ї—П";
  - `RBAC` is not translated;
  - use "—Г–Ј–µ–ї", not "–љ–Њ–і–∞";
  - use "–≤–µ–±-–Є–љ—В–µ—А—Д–µ–є—Б", not `web-–Є–љ—В–µ—А—Д–µ–є—Б` or `Web-–Є–љ—В–µ—А—Д–µ–є—Б`;
  - use `IP-–∞–і—А–µ—Б`;
  - use "—Д–∞–є–ї—Л cookie", not "cookie-—Д–∞–є–ї—Л";
  - avoid "–њ–ї–∞—В—Д–Њ—А–Љ–∞ Deckhouse"; use product names explicitly (for example, Deckhouse Kubernetes Platform).
- For mixed EN/RU or abbreviation+RU compound terms, use a hyphen:
  - `S3-–±–∞–Ї–µ—В–∞` (not `S3 –±–∞–Ї–µ—В–∞`);
  - `managed-—Б–µ—А–≤–Є—Б` (not `managed —Б–µ—А–≤–Є—Б`);
  - `master-—Г–Ј–µ–ї` (not `master —Г–Ј–µ–ї`);
  - `HTTP-–њ—А–Њ—В–Њ–Ї–Њ–ї` or `–њ—А–Њ—В–Њ–Ї–Њ–ї HTTP` (not `HTTP –њ—А–Њ—В–Њ–Ї–Њ–ї`).
- Do not replace approved terms with synonyms if glossary defines exact form.
- Keep product naming consistent with glossary and product wording rules.
- Module name must be used exactly as defined in `module.yaml.name` (canonical lowercase Kebab Case).
- Do not humanize or reformat module name in prose:
  - use `stronghold`, not `Stronghold`;
  - use `volume-data-manager`, not `Volume Data Manager`.
- For RU text, avoid jargon variants forbidden by glossary.
- If a local checklist conflicts with full glossary text, follow `.cursor/rules/docs/refs-glossary-full.mdc`.

# Language Consistency

- Use one term form throughout a page.
- Keep EN technical terms where glossary explicitly requires no translation.
- Validate key terms in headings, alerts, and examples, not only body text.
